tion by LDAMP2','1. Disconnect/connect the CR-Main FFC.<br>2. Disconnect/connect the Head FFC.<br>3. Replace Print Head.<br>4. Replace CR Relay Board.<br>5. Replace Main Board.'),(512,4,'SC-F6430','256241','Head GVDD Low Error (LDAMP2)','Main Board','Error detection by LDAMP2','Replace Main Board'),(513,4,'SC-F6430','256242','Head VBS abnormal Error (LDAMP2)','1. Head FFC<br>2. CR-Main FFC<br>3. Print Head<br>4. Main Board','Error detection by LDAMP2','1. Disconnect/connect the CR-Main FFC.<br>2. Disconnect/connect the Head FFC.<br>3. Replace Print Head.<br>4. Replace CR Relay Board.<br>5. Replace Main Board.'),(514,4,'SC-F6430','307218','Take-up unit recognition error','N/A','The Auto take-up reel unit is not recognized.','Use the supplied USB cable.'),(515,5,'SC-F6430H','001121','Roll Paper Detector Malfunction Error','1. PE Sensor (roll paper) connector<br>2. PE Sensor (roll paper) lever','During printing of the rear end (last) of a roll paper, even though the PE Sensor detects no paper, the roll paper sensor detects the presence of paper.','1. Check the cable connections (CN17) for abnormalities such as detachment of the PE Sensor (roll paper) connector, a broken cable, etc. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>2. Check the sliding condition of the PE Sensor (roll paper) lever and set the sensor lever to the correct position.<br>3. Replace the PE Sensor (roll paper)'),(516,5,'SC-F6430H','001125','CR Home Position Detection Error','1. CR HP Sensor<br>2. CR Scale<br>3. Paper jam inside the printer<br>4. CR Lock<br>5. CR Encoder','The CR HP Sensor cannot detect the CR Unit. Or, since the home contact position cannot be detected, the CR home position cannot be set.','1. Remove the jammed paper.<br>2. Check for CR HP Sensor failure (if the Shield Plate reacts to the sensor).<br>3. Check if the CR Scale is contaminated, clean it with ethanol.<br>4. Check CR Lock release.<br>After power ON, check that the CR Lock release operation was performed correctly. If not, check the Pump Cap Unit state and if it has a failure replace it.<br>5. Replace the CR Scale.<br>6. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>Check the operation state of the CR Motor.<br>7. If there is any abnormality in the CR Encoder, replace it.<br>8. Replace the CR HP Sensor.<br>9. Replace the CR Lock (Maintenance Unit).'),(517,5,'SC-F6430H','001128','Cutter Home Position Detection Error','1. Cutter Origin Sensor connector<br>2. Cutter Unit','The cutter origin cannot be detected at the time of initialization. The cutter cannot return or the sensor does not react.','1. Check for a paper jam around the Cutter Unit and if a foreign object is found, remove it.<br>2. Check the connection (CN16) of the Cutter Origin Sensor for connector disconnection, damage, or a broken cable.<br>3. Replace the Cutter Unit.'),(518,5,'SC-F6430H','001129','PG Home Position Detection Error','1. PG Sensor<br>2. APG Unit<br>3. Foreign object around the contact position when the CR origin is detected','The position cannot be detected by the PG Sensor when PG is switched. The PG Sensor cannot perform detection even though the APG Motor is driven.','1. Check for PG Sensor failure (if the Shield Plate reacts to the sensor). If the PG Sensor failed, replace it.<br>2. Is the PG planetary gear moving (Planetary Gear and the gear do not engage)? If it is not moving, replace the APG Unit.<br>3. Check if the origin of the CR Unit has been displaced (the planetary gear and the gear do not engage). Also, remove foreign objects around the contact position during CR origin detection (this printer switches PG when the carriage returns to the home position).'),(519,5,'SC-F6430H','00112B','PF Driven Release Home Position Detection Error','1. Driven Roller Sensor<br>2. Driven Roller Motor','When performing driven roller origin detection = driven roller reset operation, the sensor state and the current roller positi